The '''Penington Institute''' is a [[public health]] research and [[drug policy]] organization based in [[Carlton, Victoria]], Australia.<ref>{{cite news |title=Prescription drug overdoses on the rise in Tasmania amid 'hidden Benzo epidemic' |url=http://www.abc.net.au/news/2018-08-28/prescription-drug-overdoses-on-the-rise-in-tasmania/10170586 |accessdate=17 September 2018 |publisher=ABC |date=27 August 2018}}</ref>
The Institute produces an annual report on Australian [[drug overdose|overdose]] deaths. The 2018 report showed that deaths from overdoses, mostly from [[opioid]]s, had increased across the country consistently since 2003, and significantly outnumbered [[Automobile deaths|deaths on the road]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Australian overdose deaths are increasing – and the demographics are changing |url=https://www.racgp.org.au/newsGP/Clinical/Australian-drug-overdose-deaths-are-increasing-–-a |accessdate=17 September 2018 |publisher=Royal Australian College of General Practitioners |date=30 August 2018}}</ref> Figures are produced detailing deaths for individual areas.<ref>{{cite news |title=Brimbank drug deaths alarm |url=http://www.starweekly.com.au/news/brimbank-drug-deaths-alarm/ |accessdate=17 September 2018 |publisher=Star Weekly |date=11 September 2018}}</ref>
The Institute initiated [[International Overdose Awareness Day]] in 2015.<ref>{{cite news |title=Vigil to observe International Overdose Awareness Day |url=http://www.recordonline.com/news/20180821/vigil-to-observe-international-overdose-awareness-day |accessdate=17 September 2018 |publisher=Record online |date=21 August 2018}}</ref>
